The paper proposes a neuromorphic approach for energy-efficient mapless navigation using a combination of deep reinforcement learning and spiking neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also focuses on the application of this approach to mobile robots, which suggests the category cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the training of the networks using gradient descent, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the co-learning of the two networks, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
